annotationA: Alpha-(1,6)-fucosyltransferase; Catalyzes the addition of fucose in alpha 1-6 linkage to the first GlcNAc residue, next to the peptide chains in N-glycans. The addition is prevented if the GlcNAc residue is already fucosylated
annotationB: Glycoprotein 3-alpha-L-fucosyltransferase A; Catalyzes alpha-1,3 glycosidic linkages of N-glycans. Plays a role in neuronal development by promoting ventral nerve cord formation, possibly by promoting interactions between migrating cells and the extracellular matrix or by promoting neural activity; Belongs to the glycosyltransferase 10 family
